 <br>
   As we get older, levelwise, we have to come back to the notion of root parking as a tool more and more.  This is especially true in Luclin where you can have level 4x mobs that are immune to Mezz/charm. <br>
   <br>
   Aggro management in experience groups, like raids, is a total group effort.  I never use the aggro management spells in a group.  Teach your group to use root aggro properly and things fall into place(on the ground).<br>
<br>
  For experience camps there is one other thing that affects ones spell lineup.  Before the break and after.  Before I am much more likely to have AoE stuns and mezz up.  After I am much more likely to use nukes or charm.<br>
<br>
